#Read the data
df = pd.read_csv('drone_delivery_v1.csv', sep=';')
df = df.drop('clientid', axis = 1)

#Set the number of clusters to 3
num_clusters = 3

#Get the column names before it's too late
colnames = list(df.columns.values.tolist())
In [ ]:

In [ ]:
#Let K-means work it's magic and find locations for the depot centers
kmeans = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=num_clusters)
kmeans.fit_predict(df)
depot_centers = kmeans.cluster_centers_
print(depot_centers)

In [ ]:
#Replace k-means with agglomerative hierarchical clustering
agg_clustering = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=num_clusters)
agg_clustering.fit_predict(df)

df['cluster'] = agg_clustering.labels_

sns.scatterplot(x='x', y='y', hue='cluster', data=df)
Out[ ]:
<AxesSubplot:xlabel='x', ylabel='y'>

With agglomerative clustering the cluster borders are defined less sharply.
